				<baseName xml:lang="zh">硫化物尾矿</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Sulfidic copper tailings; SCTs</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">Sulfidic copper tailings; SCTs</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Wastes</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Mining waste</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Sulfidic tailings are high-volume wastes with a high content of sulfide minerals. They can lead to severe environmental damage if not properly managed. These tailings can undergo weathering if put in contact with oxygen and water, generating acid mine drainage (AMD). Sulfidic copper tailings with excessive sulfur content are prone to oxidation, leading to the generation of sulfates and causing compatibility issues with cement.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">硫化尾矿是硫化矿物含量较高的大量废物。如果管理不当，会对环境造成严重破坏。这些尾矿如果与氧气和水接触，就会发生风化，产生酸性矿山排水 (AMD)。硫含量过高的硫化铜尾矿容易氧化，从而产生硫酸盐，并造成与水泥的相容性问题。</common:generalComment>
